Niger State Government has presented vehicles to Magistrates in the State as part of logistics support and effort to improve the efficiency and effectiveness of the judicial workers. Presenting the vehicles to the Chief Judge of Niger State, Governor Abubakar Sani Bello called on the beneficiaries to make good use of the support to enhance quick dispensation of justice in the State, adding that his administration will continue to work tirelessly towards the upliftment of the state judiciary. He reiterated the state governmentâ€™s recognition of a robust judicial system adding that it would spare nothing at ensuring that judges and magistrates operate an efficiently financed judicial sector that will deliver adequately to the people of state. He stated that the distribution of the vehicles will continue until all other Magistrates are provided with the logistics that would encourage their movement to their respective places of assignment. According to the Governor, 15 Peugeot 406 vehicles where to be distributed in the first phase to Magistrates 1 in the state. Mrs Mary Noel BerjeChief Press Secretary Suleiman idris is a graduate of Fed Univ of Tech Minna (BTECH Mathematics/Comp Science), Specialist in ICT Support Services. also proficient in use of  online journalism tools & Social media management.  I currently serve as I.T Officer with Africa's Largest TV Network NTA